Maruku is a [Markdown] interpreter written in [Ruby].

> The official repository has moved to GitHub: <a href="http://github.com/nex3/maruku">http://github.com/nex3/maruku</a>
{#news}

> [The last GEM release](changelog.html#stable) is version 0.6.0 -- 2009-05-04.
{#news}

![data flow](diagram.png){#dataflow}




__Authors__: Maruku was started by [Andrea Censi]. The current maintaner is
<a href="http://nex-3.com/">Nathan Weizenbaum</a>. Many other people contributed patches; a partial list is in the AUTHORS file in the source distribution.

__The name of the game__: Maruku is the [romaji] transliteration of 
the [katakana] transliteration
of "Mark", the first word in Markdown. I chose this name because Ruby 
is Japanese, and also the syllable "ru" appears in Maruku.

